{
  "texts": [
    "The instances where BASE has better Rouge-LCS than ScafFix (Subset-1) have lesser values of Difficult-RS Concentration as well as Novel-RS Concentration, but higher values of Rouge-LCS overlap compared to Subset-2.",
    "Thus, for the instances that are less novel, have less OOV concentration, and are easier to infer, ScafFix is less helpful.",
    "This result from error analysis is also in line with the comparison of fine-grained settings (Table 6) reported in the main text, where we see general improvements for both Llama-2 and Llama-3.1 models for instances with higher OOV and higher novelty settings.",
    "We conducted our survey on Prolific platform foot_3 where we hired 9 medical experts from the platform across globe.",
    "All the annotators were shown 10 random samples from a pool of 30 summaries where the order of summaries was randomized and blinded (annotators have no idea which summary came from which model)."
  ]
}